name: The Chosen Pessimist
description:
Cut my throat and throw me to the wolves. I'm just too tired, too tired to reload. Don't need your tears, I don't need your love. Don't need your sympathy, I am above. I'll be the ghost that haunts you in your sleep. You have anchored the hate in me. Don't need your tears, I don't need your love. Don't need your sympathy, I am above. My God, I don't need you. I won't wait for you to come around. My God, as the pain inflates. I know I bleed, I bleed for you.

Oil on canvas.
